memberdef.name: DrawStringLine

briefdescription.para: Draw two text pairs, one left aligned and one right aligned. The strings to draw are specified by the Pair<K, V> parameters.

detaileddescription.para: A pair can be any two strings; i.e. "Customer ID:" and "Test Customer". To draw the text, this method needs to know if the left and right text should be considered as pairs. This means that the Key of the Pair<K, V> will be drawn bolded while the Value will be drawn using the regular text font.
You should also specify whether the current y-position should be updated after execution of this method.

parameterdescription.para: The text to draw left aligned.
Is the left text considered a pair?
The text to draw right aligned.
Is the right text considered a pair?
